news.title: Bengaluru: FIR filed against Lactin Developers for violating sanctioned building plan
news.para: BBMP had approved a building plan for property owners G Lakshmi Prasad and D Hardeep and A Vijaykumar, partners of GPA holder Lactin Developers, in plots nos. 6 and 7 in Mallathahalli village.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance reports Rs 44 crore net profit in Q2 FY25
news.para: For the six month period ending September 30, 2024 net profits of the company stood at Rs 111 crore as against net profits of Rs 117 crore registered a year ago.

news.title: Certus Capital invests Rs 150 crore in two residential projects in Mumbai
news.para: These mid-income housing projects near Mumbai international airport and extended western suburb of Vasai have an aggregate development of 385,000 sq ft and revenue potential of over Rs 750 crore.

news.title: Delhi court orders fresh probe in cheating case against Gautam Gambhir and others
news.para: An alleged cheating case was filed against real estate firms Rudra Buildwell Realty Pvt. Ltd, H R Infracity Pvt Ltd., U M Architectures and Contractors Ltd., and Gambhir, who was a director and brand ambassador of the companies' joint venture.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to penalise Amrapali Leisure Valley Developers for illegal borewells
news.para: A recent survey by the district administration found at least 50 villa owners at Amrapali Leisure Valley society have set up borewells for personal consumption.

news.title: Sebi issues demand notices to Reliance Home Finance's promoter, others in fund diversion case
news.para: The regulator has warned these entities for attachment of assets and bank accounts if they fail to make the payment within 15 days.

news.title: Homebuyers protest against Smart World Developers in Gurugram
news.para: The protesters claim that Smart World Developers began canceling units without prior consent starting in Sept 2024, with the cancellations persisting into Oct.

news.title: Sebi proposes measures to simplify public issue processes for small and medium REITs
news.para: SM REITs were introduced in March 2024 to encourage smaller real estate investments and increase participation in the sector. These are similar to REITs but operate on a smaller scale with a minimum asset value of Rs 50 crore compared to Rs 500 crore for regular REITs.

news.title: BigBloc Constructions doubles AAC blocks manufacturing capacity
news.para: Narayan Saboo, chairman, BigBloc Constructions said, "Along with this, we have also commissioned installation of 625KW rooftop solar plant at Wada facility."

news.title: Delhi CM approves 'anywhere registration' policy for property registration
news.para: Delhi residents will now be able to register their property at any sub-registrar office of their choice, at their convenience. Delhi Chief Minister Atishi has approved the 'Anywhere Registration' policy, which removes the requirement for citizens to visit a specific sub-registrar office.

news.title: HUDCO reports 52% increase in net profit to Rs 688 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: The company's total income rose to Rs 2,526.14 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 1,880.85 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Madurai TIDEL park to be completed by January 2026: Industries minister, Tamil Nadu
news.para: The upcoming park, which will be constructed on 5.34 lakh sq ft of land in a G+12 structure, is expected to generate around 5,000 direct jobs and 1,000 indirect employment opportunities.

news.title: Hong Kong sees fresh record home buying by mainland Chinese: Centaline Property Agency
news.para: In the first nine months, 8,133 new and second-hand homes, representing 24% of total sales, were purchased by mainland Chinese buyers, according to a Centaline survey that tracks buyers' names with Mandarin spellings.

news.title: Boston Properties posts $859.2 million revenue in Q3 2024
news.para: In the first three quarters of 2024, the REIT executed 3.3 million square feet of leasing, representing a 25% increase compared to the same period in 2023. Quarterly revenue from leases rose 4% to $799.5 million.

news.title: Government urges 29 AMRUT towns in Uttar Pradesh to submit GIS-based master plans
news.para: The Central govt has asked for the submission of the master plans by the end of this year to be eligible for financial assistance under various schemes floated by the Union ministry of housing and urban affairs.

news.title: Mormugao civic body regularises 544 housing board homes in New Vaddem
news.para: These structures were allocated to municipal workers under the Economically Weaker Sections (EWS) Housing Scheme and were approved on Tuesday in accordance with Mormugao Planning and Development Authority (MPDA) records.

news.title: Goa government to raise minimum land prices in Tiswadi, Mormugao, and Salcete
news.para: “We have decided to increase the minimum land price in Tiswadi, Mormugao, and Salcete talukas so that development can take place in other talukas, and it will even generate revenue for the state,” CM Pramod Sawant told TOI

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: UPSIDA extends residential plot registration deadline to 180 days
news.para: As per the available legal framework, any person or entity buying land for residential purposes must get the property registered and pay the required stamp duty to the govt within 120 days.

news.title: No building plans to be approved in industrial areas without jurisdiction: Karnataka HC
news.para: ​​This decision followed a state government notification in July, based on recommendations from a court-appointed committee, which confirmed these organisations’ exclusive authority over building plan approvals.

news.title: West Bengal CM orders construction of homes for those excluded from PMAY
news.para: "The state government has decided to build houses for all people in the state who have been deprived of the Centre's Awas Yojana. The CM issued strict instructions today, asserting that the central government is not providing any funds and will not impose any conditions," he said.
